#10126
@@yThe Undercroft Entry@@N~
The entry chamber to the pyramid's undercroft is hewn from living bedrock, its ceiling reinforced with @@bsandstone@@N beams that have bowed but not yet broken under millennia of weight. @@yGold-leaf hieroglyphs@@N, long since reduced to faint outlines, mark the upper walls above empty torch brackets still aligned with the precision of original construction. The chamber was a controlled point of descent once; fitted grooves in the floor show where barriers were meant to stand. Overhead, a @@bheavy trapdoor@@N of iron-banded timber is set flush into the stone ceiling, its surface dark with age and sealed with a @@bbronze@@N lock mechanism corroded to a deep verdigris. Passages lead east into the flooded antechamber and south into the deeper levels of the undercroft.
