@@yA Flooded Antechamber@@N~
Black water stands ankle-deep across the entire floor, fed by seepage through hairline cracks in the @@bsandstone@@N walls that weep a slow, constant mineral damp. The ceiling is lower here than in the adjacent passages, pressing the air down to a stale intimacy thick with the smell of iron and old stone. @@cFaint blue-green lines@@N of mineral deposit mark the high-water stains on the walls, recording past floods at intervals that tell a history of seasonal catastrophe. The western passage leads back toward the entry chamber; corridors continue east and south into the undercroft's deeper reaches.
