Ancient tree roots from the desert surface have found their way deep into the pyramid's foundations here, cracking the @@bsandstone@@N blocks apart in a slow catastrophe of arrested growth. The roots themselves are long dead, their fibrous trunks pale and desiccated, yet they have pried the corridor walls open by several hand-widths. Thin curtains of @@yfine sand@@N perpetually sift through the gaps in the stone, accumulating in pale drifts along both walls. Underfoot, shattered stone fragments make every step uncertain.
