@@yThe Wind-Scoured Chamber@@N~
Cracks in the ceiling of this chamber let in thin columns of @@yhot desert air@@N and, on windy days, narrow shafts of direct sunlight that move across the floor in slow arcs as the sun passes. The effect of the light column on the carved @@yyellow@@N surfaces is dramatic: the gold leaf seems to generate the light rather than reflect it for the duration of the shaft's passage. The crack pattern in the ceiling follows the stress lines of the pyramid's settling, and @@bsand@@N has accumulated in small drifts below each crack, importing the desert directly into the apex.
~
