#10314
@@yThe Golden Hall@@N~
Gold leaf lines every surface of this chamber: ceiling, walls, floor borders, column shafts, every carved element. The @@yyellow@@N coverage is complete enough that the underlying @@bsandstone@@N is invisible; the room is entirely constructed, perceptually, from gold. The carved reliefs visible in the gold-covered surfaces depict the pyramid's divine patron in every aspect — creative, destructive, judging, blessing — the full range of divine authority expressed through a single medium at its maximum density. The room is simultaneously the most ornate and the most restrained in the pyramid, all variation subsumed into the single color of absolute divine authority.
~
