@@yA Side Niche@@N~
A small dark recess at the junction of two apex corridors, its interior walls carrying the densest concentration of @@yyellow@@N paint on the floor — the gold color here has been applied so many times that it has built up to a texture visible to the touch. The niche held something specific; the mounting hardware is still present, sized for an object roughly the dimensions of a modest sculpture. Whatever it held was removed, but the accumulation of devotional gold paint records how important the object was to whoever tended this space.
