#10317
@@yThe Hall of Judgment@@N~
The final carvings depicting the afterlife journey cover both walls of this hall from floor to ceiling: the soul's arrival before the divine court, the weighing of the heart, the declaration of worthiness, and the final passage into the eternal field that awaits the righteous. The sequence is the most narrative and most visually complex carving in the entire pyramid, rendered with an intimacy and detail that suggests the artists were working from genuine belief rather than contractual obligation. @@yGold@@N fills the divine court, @@cblue@@N fills the eternal field, and @@bochre@@N fills the mortal figures making their passage between them.
~
