@@yThe Pharaoh's Antechamber@@N~
A formal antechamber immediately before the apex's inner halls, its walls carrying the portrait of the Sand Sovereign in its living form: an architect, shown with tools of measurement and construction, surrounded by the implements of the pyramid's design. The portrait is unlike any other in the pyramid — the subject is shown working rather than receiving, creating rather than commanding. @@yGold@@N fills every surface of the work's background, and the Sovereign's figure is the only element rendered in natural pigment colors: brown skin, @@cblue@@N headdress, @@yyellow@@N regalia. The portrait's intent appears to be pride rather than authority.
~
